\eqn{\Sigma_s} from centroid distances.
\item Obtain the lower Cholesky factor \eqn{L = \text{chol}(\Sigma_s)^\top}.
\item At each year \eqn{t}, draw a spatially correlated innovation
\eqn{z_t \sim \mathcal{N}(0, \Sigma_s)} via \eqn{L z}, \eqn{z \sim
   \mathcal{N}(0, I)}.
\item Apply an AR(1) filter across years with coefficient \code{temporal_rho}.
\item Superimpose a cell-shared linear trend scaled by \code{trend_sd}.
